{"TopicId":140020,"ForumId":50,"TopicTitle":"How do i \u0026#039;control\u0026#039; a kerbal","CreatedByName":"Jeb-head-mug kerman","CreatedById":159289,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-18T10:37:42Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Jeb-head-mug kerman","CreatedById":159289,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-18T10:37:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you guys know how to use rcs on a kerbal?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lunar Sea","CreatedById":164137,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-18T13:56:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Extra-Vehicular_Activity#Controls\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Extra-Vehicular_Activity#Controls\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBasically WASD to go backwards forwards left and right. Shift \u0026amp; Ctrl to go up and down. Q\u0026amp;E to rotate.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-18T23:17:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe R key turns RCS packs on and off, then it\u0027s the keystrokes Lunar Sea mentions. With the pack off, Kerbals are inert in space.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jeb-head-mug kerman","CreatedById":159289,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-19T06:31:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk but I\u0027ve tried W for forwards but it always seems to go more up than forwards.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lunar Sea","CreatedById":164137,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-19T15:29:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222590146\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140020\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221463639463\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022159289\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jeb-head-mug kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Jeb-head-mug kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk but I\u0027ve tried W for forwards but it always seems to go more up than forwards.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSometimes the camera angle can be decieving. Also depends what you are referencing to - if it\u0027s moving too than can complicate things.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jeb-head-mug kerman","CreatedById":159289,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-20T00:04:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dispatcher","CreatedById":78707,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T03:20:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do I control a Kerbal? \u00A0Bribing with tasty treats works well for me!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbinchaser","CreatedById":160817,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T03:59:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAgreed. I sometimes give Jeb a booster or two, and he\u0027ll be under my control for the rest of the day. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}